Fighting Challenge +%1		KEY:Knight ~ Fighting Challenge		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DEFINE:FightingChallengeLVL|0	DEFINE:FightingChallenge|0	DEFINE:ChallengeDuration|0	DESC:As a swift action, you can issue a challenge against a single opponent. The target must have an Intelligence of 5 or higher, have a language of some sort, and a CR greater than or equal to your character level -2. If it does not meet these requirements, a use of thie ability is expended without effect. If the target is eligible, you gain a +%1 morale bonus on Will saves, attack and damage rolls against the target. If you are reduced to 0 hp by the designated target, you loose 2 Knight's Challenges for the day due to loss of ego. The effect lasts up to %2 rounds.|FightingChallenge|ChallengeDuration																																											BONUS:VAR|ChallengeDuration|(5+CHA)		SOURCEPAGE:p.25	ASPECT:NAME|Fighting Challenge +%1|FightingChallengeLVL		BONUS:VAR|FightingChallengeLVL|1+(KnightLVL>6)+(KnightLVL>12)+(KnightLVL>18)
Knight's Challenge		KEY:Knight ~ Knight's Challenge		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DEFINE:KnightsChallenges|0											DESC:Your dauntless fighting spirit plays a major role in your fighting style, as important as the strength in your arm or the sharpness of your blade. You can call out a foe, shouting a challenge that boosts his confidence or issue a challenge that strikes fear into weak opponents and compels strong opponents to seek you out for personal combat. By playing on your enemies' ego, you manipulate your foes. You have a total of %1 uses per day of Knight's challenge.|KnightsChallenges																																																																BONUS:VAR|KnightsChallenges|((CL/2)+CHA)	SOURCEPAGE:p.25
Knight's Code			KEY:Knight ~ Knight's Code			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																DESC:You fight not only to defeat your foes but prove your honor. The knight's code focuses on fair play; A victory achieved through pure skill is more difficult, and hence wins more glory than one achieved through trickery or guile. A knight does not gain flanking bonus (though he confers it to others). A knight never strikes a flat-footed opponent. Instead he allows his foe to ready himself first. A knight never deals lethal damage to a helpless foe. If a knight violates any part of his code, he loses a challenge use for the day. If you run out of challenge uses, you take a -2 penalty on attack rolls and saves for the remainder of the day.																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.27
Shield Block +%1			KEY:Knight ~ Shield Block			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DEFINE:ShieldBlockLVL|0	DEFINE:ShieldBoost|0								DESC:Starging at 2nd level, you excel in using your armor and shield to frustrate your enemy's attacks. During your action, designate a single opponent and gain a shield bonus to AC equal to %1.|ShieldBoost																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.27	ASPECT:NAME|Shield Block +%1|ShieldBlockLVL		BONUS:VAR|ShieldBlockLVL|1+(KnightLVL>10)+(KnightLVL>19)
Bulwark of Defense		KEY:Knight ~ Bulwark of Defense		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																DESC:When you reach 3rd level, an opponent that begins its turn in your threatened area treats all the squares that you threaten as difficult terrain. Your strict vigilance and active defensive maneuvers force your opponents to move with care.																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.28
Armor Mastery			KEY:Knight ~ Armor Mastery			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DEFINE:ArmorMasteryLVL|0											DESC:Starting at 4th level, you are able to wear your armor like a second skin and ignore the standard speed reduction for wearing medium armor.	DESC:Your ability to wear armor as a second skin and not be slowed by it now extends to heavy armor.|PREVAREQ:ArmorMasteryLVL,2																																																																																		ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Knight ~ Armor Mastery (Heavy)|PREVAREQ:ArmorMasteryLVL,2								SOURCEPAGE:p.28	ASPECT:NAME|Armor Mastery (Medium)|PREVAREQ:ArmorMasteryLVL,1	ASPECT:NAME|Armor Mastery (Heavy)|PREVAREQ:ArmorMasteryLVL,2	UNENCUMBEREDMOVE:MediumArmor		BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Walk|10|PREARMORTYPE:1,TYPE.Medium	BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Walk|10|PREARMORTYPE:1,TYPE.Heavy,TYPE.Exotic|PREVARGTEQ:ArmorMasteryLVL,2		BONUS:VAR|ArmorMasteryLVL|1+(KnightLVL>8)
Armor Mastery (Heavy)		KEY:Knight ~ Armor Mastery (Heavy)		CATEGORY:Special Ability																																																																																																																																																																																																										UNENCUMBEREDMOVE:HeavyArmor
Test of Mettle			KEY:Knight ~ Test of Mettle			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DEFINE:ChallengeDuration|0											DESC:Starting at 4th level, you can shout a challenge to all enemies, calling out for the mightiest among them to face you in combat. Any target must have a Int score of 5 or more and speak a language. You must also have line of sight and effect to your target. As a swift action, you expend a use of Knight's Challenge to cause all enemies within 100 feet with a CR greater than or equal to your character level -2 to make Will saves (DC 10+(CL/2)+CHA). Creatures that fail the save are forced to attack you in preference over other targets. If you are reduced to 0 or fewer hit points by an opponent forced to attack you in this manor, you gain an additional challenge use for the day from having proved your mettle. The effect lasts %1 rounds.|Challenge Duration																	BONUS:VAR|ChallengeDuration|(5+CHA)		SOURCEPAGE:p.26
Vigilant Defender			KEY:Knight ~ Vigilant Defender		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																DESC:Starting at 5th level, you stand your ground against all enemies, warding the spot where you make your stand to prevent foes from slipping past and attacking those you protect. If an opponent attempts to use the Tumble skill to move through your threatened area or your space, the DC increases by an amount equal to your class level.																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.28
Shield Ally				KEY:Knight ~ Shield Ally			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																DESC:Starting at 6th level, as an immediate action you can optto absorb part of the damage dealt to an adjacent ally. Each time this ally takes damage from a physical attack before your next turn, you can take half this damage on yourself. You can only absorb damage from physical attacks, not spells or other effects.																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.28
Improved Shield Ally		KEY:Knight ~ Improved Shield Ally		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																DESC:At 14th level, your ability to absorb damage increases. Once per round you can absorb all the damage from a single attack directed against an adjacent ally. In addition, you continue to absorb half the damage from other physical attacks on an adjacent ally.																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.28
Call to Battle			KEY:Knight ~ Call to Battle			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																DESC:Starting at 8th level, you become an inspiring figure on the battlefield. WHen all seems lost, you are a beacon of hope who continues to fight on despite the odds. As a swift action, you expend a challenge use to grant an ally another save against a fear effect. They get a bonus on the save equal to your Charisma mod on the extra save.																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.26
Daunting Challenge		KEY:Knight ~ Daunting Challenge		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																DESC:Starting at 12th level, you can call out opponents, striking fear into the hearts of your enemies. In this manner you separate the strong-minded from the weak willed, allowing you to focus on worthy foes. As a swift action, you expend a challenge use. This ability affects all creatures within 100 feet of you with a CR less than your level -2. Targest must be able to hear you, understand you, and have an Intelligence of 5 or more. They must make Will saves (DC 10+(CL/2)+CHA) or become shaken.																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.26
Bond of Loyalty			KEY:Knight ~ Bond of Loyalty			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																DESC:Starting at 16th level, your loyalty to your comrades endures even in the face of powerful magic. You may expend a challenge use as a free action to make an additional save against a mind-affecting spell or ability.																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.27
Impetuous Endurance		KEY:Knight ~ Impetuous Endurance		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																DESC:Starting at 17th level, your fighting spirit enables you to push your body beyond the normal limits of endurance. You no longer automatically fail a saving throw on a roll of 1. You might still fail if the total isn't sufficient to beat the DC.																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.28
Loyal Beyond Death		KEY:Knight ~ Loyal Beyond Death		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Knight Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																DESC:At 20th level, if you are reduced to 0 or fewer hit points by an effect that otherwise leaves your body intact, you can expend a challenge use to continue to act for 1 more round before dying, even if your hit point total is -10 or lower. You can continue to do this until your run out of challenge uses.																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.27

